Usage: loadPtnPin [-help] [-report <string>] [-snapModifiedToBoundary] { [-ptnName <string> ] | -all } { -file <string> | -def <string> }

-help                       # Prints out the command usage
-all                        # Specifies to load all partitions.
                            # (bool, optional)
-def <string>               # Specifies the full pathname of the partition def
                            # file . (string, optional)
-file <string>              # Specifies the full pathname of the partition
                            # floorplan file . (string, optional)
-ptnName <string>           # Specifies the name of the partition.
                            # (string, optional)
-report <string>            # Specifies the optional report filename that
                            # contains any pins deleted or newly added.
                            # (string, optional)
-snapModifiedToBoundary     # Snap pins to modified partition boundary.
                            # (bool, optional)